law.text:
The Governor, upon the recommendation of the Secretary or a majority of the Board, may remove any member of the Board for any of the following reasons:
Conviction of a crime involving moral turpitude, or any criminal offense the effect of which is to prevent or interfere with the performance of Board duties;
Failure to attend regularly scheduled meetings of the Board;
Failure to carry out duties assigned by the Board or its chairman; or
Acceptance of another office or the conduct of other business conflicting with or tending to conflict with performance of any duty of the Board.
